Zombie storms are rising from the dead thanks to climate change


By

Yasemin Saplakoglu 





Wildfires are burning the West Coast, hurricanes are flooding the Southeast — and some of those storms are rising from the dead.

By

Yasemin Saplakoglu

Nicoletta Lanese

Rachael Rettner

Mike McRae
